00:15:27.286 --> 00:15:29.676 A:middle
So to initiate a
broadcast programmatically,

00:15:30.046 --> 00:15:32.416 A:middle
we use a new class
called RPBroadcastActivity

00:15:32.416 --> 00:15:34.506 A:middle
ViewController, and
call its load method

00:15:34.506 --> 00:15:35.446 A:middle
to get an instance of it.

00:15:36.266 --> 00:15:39.386 A:middle
We then simply present it as you
would any UI view controller,

00:15:40.116 --> 00:15:41.646 A:middle
which will then present
the user with a list

00:15:41.646 --> 00:15:43.926 A:middle
of broadcast services, and
ultimately allow the user

00:15:44.146 --> 00:15:45.166 A:middle
to set up the broadcast.

00:15:46.306 --> 00:15:47.566 A:middle
Just before we do that, though,

00:15:47.646 --> 00:15:49.566 A:middle
we also set the
ActivityViewController's

00:15:49.706 --> 00:15:50.376 A:middle
delegate method.

00:15:50.416 --> 00:15:53.596 A:middle
Because we want to be notified
when the setup is complete.

00:15:55.436 --> 00:15:57.536 A:middle
At this point, the user
can select the service

00:15:57.536 --> 00:15:59.916 A:middle
to broadcast to, sets
up the broadcast,

00:16:00.096 --> 00:16:01.606 A:middle
and once we you done setting up,

00:16:02.176 --> 00:16:04.346 A:middle
the activity view controller's
delegate method is fired,

00:16:05.286 --> 00:16:07.376 A:middle
and this delegate method
is supplied an incidence

00:16:07.376 --> 00:16:10.206 A:middle
of another new class,
RPBroadcastController,

00:16:10.606 --> 00:16:12.316 A:middle
which allows us to
start a broadcast.

00:16:12.996 --> 00:16:15.006 A:middle
But before we do that,
though, we also want

00:16:15.006 --> 00:16:17.506 A:middle
to dismiss the
ActivityViewController,

00:16:17.886 --> 00:16:19.506 A:middle
since we are the ones
that presented it.

00:16:20.166 --> 00:16:21.816 A:middle
Start our in game
countdown timer,

00:16:22.606 --> 00:16:24.246 A:middle
and when the countdown
timer ends,

00:16:24.856 --> 00:16:28.256 A:middle
