UI to also indicate an

00:16:48.996 --> 00:16:50.206 A:middle
in progress broadcast,

00:16:50.606 --> 00:16:52.276 A:middle
maximizing the available
screen space.

00:16:53.346 --> 00:16:55.946 A:middle
Something to note is that the
indicator is strictly required

00:16:55.946 --> 00:16:58.966 A:middle
during broadcasting and will
be enforced during app review

00:17:00.296 --> 00:17:01.596 A:middle
before you add this
to your games.

00:17:01.596 --> 00:17:05.326 A:middle
So programmatically check
if broadcast is in progress,

00:17:05.496 --> 00:17:07.506 A:middle
simply query is broadcasting
prompt

00:17:07.506 --> 00:17:08.636 A:middle
of the broadcast controller.

00:17:09.435 --> 00:17:11.965 A:middle
You can use the value of
this property to start

00:17:12.326 --> 00:17:14.776 A:middle
or stop animating
your indicator UI.

00:17:16.576 --> 00:17:18.695 A:middle
To allow users to
finish broadcasting,

00:17:18.816 --> 00:17:21.215 A:middle
the Flair developers have
implemented a fly out UI

00:17:21.215 --> 00:17:23.886 A:middle
that reveals a sub menu
which includes a stop button.

00:17:24.736 --> 00:17:26.386 A:middle
When the player presses
on the stop button,

00:17:27.136 --> 00:17:30.366 A:middle
we simply call finish
broadcast on the controller.

00:17:31.426 --> 00:17:33.666 A:middle
When broadcasting is
finished, we update our UI.

00:17:33.666 --> 00:17:36.846 A:middle
Alright, now that we
covered the basic flow,

00:17:36.996 --> 00:17:39.696 A:middle
let's look at a few more
details, like error handling.

00:17:41.656 --> 00:17:43.956 A:middle
So since there are a lot of
moving parts to this feature,

00:17:44.146 --> 00:17:45.726 A:middle
it's possible that
things could go wrong.

00:17:45.726 --> 00:17:47.936 A:middle
So it is important to
handle this gracefully.

00:17:48.546 --> 00:17:51.586 A:middle
And so let's take a look at how
we do this during a broadcast.

00:17:52.716 --> 00:17:54.586 A:middle
To handle errors,
simply set the delegate

00:17:54.586 --> 00:17:55.786 A:middle
to the broadcast controller.

00:17:55.866 --> 00:17:59.736 A:middle
Once set, your delegate
will now have its did finish

00:17:59.736 --> 00:18:03.926 A:middle
with error method called
and when this is triggered,

