with error method called
and when this is triggered,

00:18:03.926 --> 00:18:05.496 A:middle
you should let the
user know about it

00:18:05.596 --> 00:18:06.976 A:middle
and update any necessary UI.

00:18:07.626 --> 00:18:10.816 A:middle
So now another detail
to consider is

00:18:10.816 --> 00:18:12.246 A:middle
when the user backgrounds
the app,

00:18:12.246 --> 00:18:14.606 A:middle
or the app is interrupted
during a broadcast,

00:18:14.936 --> 00:18:16.546 A:middle
like when receiving a
phone call, or example.

00:18:16.586 --> 00:18:19.616 A:middle
So when the application
goes to the background,

00:18:19.616 --> 00:18:21.996 A:middle
ReplayKit will automatically
pause the broadcast.

00:18:21.996 --> 00:18:24.286 A:middle
So in this particular example,

00:18:24.286 --> 00:18:26.476 A:middle
when the application is
reactivated and comes back

00:18:26.476 --> 00:18:29.256 A:middle
to the foreground, we prompt
the user and ask if they would

00:18:29.256 --> 00:18:30.516 A:middle
like to resume the broadcast.

00:18:30.676 --> 00:18:33.506 A:middle
If the user wants
to resume, call,

00:18:33.506 --> 00:18:35.856 A:middle
the resume broadcast
method, if they don't,

00:18:36.086 --> 00:18:38.216 A:middle
simply call the finish
broadcast method.

00:18:38.466 --> 00:18:40.456 A:middle
And that's it.

00:18:40.756 --> 00:18:43.186 A:middle
For the entire flow, the game
developer needs to only interact

00:18:43.186 --> 00:18:45.196 A:middle
with two classes,
and its delegates.

00:18:45.566 --> 00:18:47.466 A:middle
RPBroadcastActivity
ViewController,

00:18:47.916 --> 00:18:50.276 A:middle
to present broadcast services,
and allow users to set

00:18:50.276 --> 00:18:53.796 A:middle
up a broadcast, and
RPBroadcastController to start,

00:18:53.886 --> 00:18:56.086 A:middle
pause, resume and
finish a broadcast.

00:18:57.156 --> 00:18:59.866 A:middle
As you can see, it couldn't
be easier to add broadcasting

00:18:59.866 --> 00:19:01.796 A:middle
into your games, and
I urge you to do so,

00:18:59.866 --> 00:19:01.796 A:middle
into your games, and
I urge you to do so,

00:19:01.796 --> 00:19:03.456 A:middle
because the benefits are huge.

00:19:03.716 --> 00:19:05.856 A:middle
There is really no better
way to spread the word,

00:19:06.466 --> 00:19:07.986 A:middle
increase player engagement

00:19:08.256 --> 00:19:10.536 A:middle
and even build a
community around your games.

00:19:10.856 --> 00:19:14.636 A:middle
So that covers game
implementation,

00:19:14.806 --> 00:19:16.436 A:middle
but what about the
broadcast services

00:19:16.536 --> 00:19:18.716 A:middle
that players are streaming
