00:19:47.846 --> 00:19:50.366 A:middle
of by ReplayKit's
BroadcastActivityViewController.

00:19:51.306 --> 00:19:53.136 A:middle
So this leaves us with
two remaining tasks.

00:19:53.926 --> 00:19:57.626 A:middle
Setting up the broadcast, and
uploading video and audio data

00:19:57.626 --> 00:19:58.616 A:middle
to the back-up servers.

00:19:59.096 --> 00:20:02.586 A:middle
So to allow broadcast services
to accomplish these steps,

00:19:59.096 --> 00:20:02.586 A:middle
So to allow broadcast services
to accomplish these steps,

00:20:02.586 --> 00:20:03.746 A:middle
we're introducing a new pair

00:20:03.746 --> 00:20:05.976 A:middle
of app extensions
specifically for this feature.

00:20:07.296 --> 00:20:10.596 A:middle
A UI extension, to allow the
user to set up a broadcast,

00:20:11.806 --> 00:20:13.686 A:middle
and a non-UI extension
for processing

00:20:13.876 --> 00:20:16.606 A:middle
and uploading the
audio and video data.

00:20:18.026 --> 00:20:20.306 A:middle
For those of you
unfamiliar with extensions,

00:20:20.606 --> 00:20:23.896 A:middle
they're target embedded in your
parent application and are a way

00:20:24.106 --> 00:20:26.446 A:middle
to extend your app so that
you can execute alongside

00:20:26.446 --> 00:20:26.986 A:middle
other apps.

00:20:27.876 --> 00:20:30.456 A:middle
They run in a separate
process from your parent app,

00:20:30.886 --> 00:20:32.916 A:middle
but can share data with
your parent application,

00:20:33.016 --> 00:20:34.386 A:middle
which can be handy
or sharing things

00:20:34.386 --> 00:20:35.956 A:middle
like authentication
data, for example.

00:20:37.156 --> 00:20:38.836 A:middle
So one thing to keep
in mind, though,

00:20:39.206 --> 00:20:40.346 A:middle
is that extensions are limited

00:20:40.346 --> 00:20:42.126 A:middle
in resources compared
to applications.

00:20:42.126 --> 00:20:45.326 A:middle
So try to refrain from doing
resource intensive tasks

00:20:45.326 --> 00:20:46.246 A:middle
within them.

00:20:47.196 --> 00:20:49.086 A:middle
We made it incredibly
easy to set

00:20:49.086 --> 00:20:50.916 A:middle
up these extensions
via an exotemplate.

00:20:51.676 --> 00:20:55.056 A:middle
These are available as new
targets for both iOS and tvOS.

00:20:56.326 --> 00:20:57.776 A:middle
If created from this template,

00:20:57.776 --> 00:21:00.206 A:middle
the extensions will be
pre-configured so they will show

00:20:57.776 --> 00:21:00.206 A:middle
the extensions will be
pre-configured so they will show

00:21:00.206 --> 00:21:02.316 A:middle
up in the broadcast
activity control list.

00:21:03.986 --> 00:21:06.516 A:middle
So let's take a look at
the two new extensions

00:21:06.516 --> 00:21:08.136 A:middle
that a broadcast service
needs to implement,

00:21:08.696 --> 00:21:10.726 A:middle
starting with the
broadcast UI extension.

00:21:12.196 --> 00:21:14.876 A:middle
UI extension has a few
key responsibilities,

00:21:15.106 --> 00:21:17.326 A:middle
first it's responsible for
